<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-11-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-11-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="90" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d90">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">823.01/11–1048: Circular telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Certain <gloss type="to">Diplomatic
                                    Representatives in the American Republics</gloss>
                            </hi><note n="1" xml:id="d90fn1">Sent to Embassies in Brazil, Chile,
                                Colombia, Costa Rica, Cuba, Mexico, Nicaragua, Panama, Uruguay,
                                Venezuela, Ecuador, El Salvador, Guatemala, Haiti, Honduras,
                                Paraguay; repeated for information to Embassies in Argentina,
                                Dominican Republic, Peru, and Bolivia.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-11-10">November 10,
                                1948</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Dept considering resumption normal diplomatic relations with Peru
                            accordance Resolution 35 Bogotá Conference. Before taking action desires
                            know attitude other <gloss target="#t_AmReps1">Amer Republics</gloss>
                            which have not yet taken action. Consult <gloss target="#t_FonMin1">FonMin</gloss> re foregoing and tel any views he may express.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>